  <main>
    <section class="section">
      <h1>AI Coding Model Comparison: 26 Models Tested on Real Bugs</h1>
      <p>We tested 26 models from 8 vendors on 32 real-world debugging tasks. Each model received shell access and one instruction: <em>find the needle</em>. The test suite passes or it doesn&rsquo;t. No subjective scoring, no LLM-as-judge, no vibes.</p>
      <p>Every model was tested in two conditions: <strong>bare</strong> (generic prompt + bash) and <strong>OS</strong> (same prompt, but project context silently injected). The model can&rsquo;t tell which arm it&rsquo;s in. 26 models &times; 32 benchmarks &times; 2 arms = 1,664 total runs.</p>
      <p><a href="/">See the full leaderboard</a> &middot; <a href="/about/">Read the methodology</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Top 10: bare performance</h2>
      <p>Without any project context, how well can each model debug from scratch?</p>
      <div class="data-table-wrap">
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Model</th><th>Vendor</th><th>Bare</th><th>Benchmarks</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>DeepSeek R1</td><td>DeepSeek</td><td class="num">96.9%</td><td class="num">31/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Grok 4.1 Fast</td><td>xAI</td><td class="num">96.9%</td><td class="num">31/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>DeepSeek V3.2</td><td>DeepSeek</td><td class="num">93.8%</td><td class="num">30/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Claude Opus 4</td><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">90.6%</td><td class="num">29/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gemini 3.1 Pro</td><td>Google</td><td class="num">87.5%</td><td class="num">28/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Claude Sonnet 4.5</td><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">78.1%</td><td class="num">25/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Qwen 3.5 Plus</td><td>Alibaba</td><td class="num">65.6%</td><td class="num">21/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>GPT-4.1</td><td>OpenAI</td><td class="num">50.0%</td><td class="num">16/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Grok 4 Fast</td><td>xAI</td><td class="num">46.9%</td><td class="num">15/32</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Claude Haiku 4.5</td><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">40.6%</td><td class="num">13/32</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="muted">DeepSeek R1 and Grok 4.1 Fast lead bare performance at 96.9%, solving 31 of 32 benchmarks without any project context. Both are reasoning models that spend more time thinking before acting.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Top 10: with context injection (OS arm)</h2>
      <p>When project context (README, file listing, test output) is silently injected into the system prompt:</p>
      <div class="data-table-wrap">
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Model</th><th>Vendor</th><th>OS</th><th>Δ from bare</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Claude Opus 4</td><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+9.4pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Claude Sonnet 4.5</td><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+21.9pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>DeepSeek V3.2</td><td>DeepSeek</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+6.2pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gemini 3.1 Pro</td><td>Google</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+12.5pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Grok 4.1 Fast</td><td>xAI</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+3.1pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>DeepSeek R1</td><td>DeepSeek</td><td class="num">96.9%</td><td class="num">+0.0pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Claude Sonnet 4</td><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">93.8%</td><td class="num green">+75.0pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gemini 3 Flash</td><td>Google</td><td class="num">93.8%</td><td class="num green">+59.4pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Claude Haiku 4.5</td><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">90.6%</td><td class="num green">+50.0pp</td></tr>
