    <section class="section">
      <h2>Biggest gainers: who benefits most from context?</h2>
      <p>Context injection doesn&rsquo;t help every model equally. The models that benefit most are those that are capable but lack the ability to efficiently explore a codebase from scratch.</p>
      <div class="data-table-wrap">
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Model</th><th>Bare</th><th>OS</th><th>Δ</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Claude Sonnet 4</td><td class="num">18.8%</td><td class="num">93.8%</td><td class="num green">+75.0pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Devstral Medium</td><td class="num">3.1%</td><td class="num">75.0%</td><td class="num green">+71.9pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Qwen3 Coder Flash</td><td class="num">9.4%</td><td class="num">81.2%</td><td class="num green">+71.9pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Mistral Large</td><td class="num">9.4%</td><td class="num">78.1%</td><td class="num green">+68.8pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>GPT-4o</td><td class="num">15.6%</td><td class="num">81.2%</td><td class="num green">+65.6pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gemini 2.5 Flash</td><td class="num">0.0%</td><td class="num">65.6%</td><td class="num green">+65.6pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Qwen Plus</td><td class="num">3.1%</td><td class="num">68.8%</td><td class="num green">+65.6pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Qwen3 Coder Plus</td><td class="num">0.0%</td><td class="num">59.4%</td><td class="num green">+59.4pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gemini 3 Flash</td><td class="num">34.4%</td><td class="num">93.8%</td><td class="num green">+59.4pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Claude Haiku 4.5</td><td class="num">40.6%</td><td class="num">90.6%</td><td class="num green">+50.0pp</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>The pattern: mid-tier and budget models gain the most. Claude Haiku 4.5 at $0.80/MTok goes from 40.6% to 90.6% with context &mdash; matching Claude Opus 4&rsquo;s bare performance at a fraction of the cost. GPT-4o jumps from 15.6% to 81.2%. These models <em>can</em> debug &mdash; they just need to be pointed at the right files.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Vendor breakdown</h2>
      <p>All eight vendors had at least one model that improved with context injection. The effect is not vendor-specific.</p>
      <div class="data-table-wrap">
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Vendor</th><th>Models</th><th>Best bare</th><th>Best OS</th><th>Mean Δ</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Anthropic</td><td class="num">4</td><td class="num">90.6%</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+39.1pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>DeepSeek</td><td class="num">3</td><td class="num">96.9%</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+10.4pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Google</td><td class="num">5</td><td class="num">87.5%</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+44.4pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>xAI</td><td class="num">2</td><td class="num">96.9%</td><td class="num">100.0%</td><td class="num green">+14.1pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>OpenAI</td><td class="num">2</td><td class="num">50.0%</td><td class="num">87.5%</td><td class="num green">+51.6pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Mistral</td><td class="num">2</td><td class="num">9.4%</td><td class="num">78.1%</td><td class="num green">+37.5pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Meta</td><td class="num">2</td><td class="num">15.6%</td><td class="num">43.8%</td><td class="num green">+14.1pp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Alibaba</td><td class="num">6</td><td class="num">65.6%</td><td class="num">81.2%</td><td class="num green">+29.9pp</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Models that didn&rsquo;t improve</h2>
      <p>Three models showed zero or negative delta:</p>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <li><strong>DeepSeek R1</strong> (96.9% &rarr; 96.9%, +0.0pp) &mdash; already near ceiling. The one benchmark it misses, it misses in both arms. Context doesn&rsquo;t help when you&rsquo;re already solving everything.</li>
        <li><strong>Llama 3.3 70B</strong> (3.1% &rarr; 3.1%, +0.0pp) &mdash; tool use is too weak to benefit from better context. Solves one benchmark in both arms through brute force.</li>
        <li><strong>Qwen 3.5 Plus</strong> (65.6% &rarr; 34.4%, &minus;31.2pp) &mdash; the only model that <em>degraded</em> with context. The injected context appears to confuse its reasoning on benchmarks it could solve bare. Under investigation.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key takeaways</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        <li><strong>Context injection is the highest-leverage intervention in AI debugging.</strong> Mean +34.3pp across 26 models. No other technique we&rsquo;ve tested comes close.</li>
        <li><strong>Budget models + context ≈ frontier models bare.</strong> Haiku 4.5 with context (90.6%) matches Opus 4 bare (90.6%). GPT-4o with context (81.2%) exceeds GPT-4.1 bare (50.0%).</li>
        <li><strong>The effect is universal.</strong> 23 of 26 models improved. All 8 vendors represented. This is not an Anthropic trick or a Claude optimization.</li>
        <li><strong>Ceiling models don&rsquo;t benefit.</strong> If you&rsquo;re already at 96.9%, there&rsquo;s nothing to gain. Context injection matters most in the 0&ndash;70% range.</li>
        <li><strong>Not all context is helpful.</strong> Qwen 3.5 Plus degraded by 31.2pp, suggesting that naive context injection can hurt models with certain reasoning patterns.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Try it yourself</h2>
      <p>The benchmark suite is open source. Run any model on any benchmark:</p>
      <div class="card">
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/os-tack/find-the-needle
cd find-the-needle
# Run a single benchmark
python3 run.py --model claude-haiku-4-5 --bench off-by-one-pagination --arm bare
python3 run.py --model claude-haiku-4-5 --bench off-by-one-pagination --arm silent</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p>Results are deterministic. Run the same benchmark twice and you&rsquo;ll get the same score. <a href="/contribute/">Contribute a benchmark</a> or <a href="https://github.com/os-tack/find-the-needle">browse the source</a>.</p>
      <p>The context injection in the OS arm is provided by <a href="https://ostk.ai">ostk</a>, a local-first OS for AI agents. <a href="https://ostk.ai/docs/">Read the docs</a> or <a href="https://ostk.ai/insights/">see more insights</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
